title: Statement of Intent: US and Ukraine industrial base

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

According to a December 8 press release by the Defense Department, on December 6, "US. and Ukrainian officials signed a statement of intent on exploring the co-production of critical weapons and on prioritizing technical and data exchange to address the urgent needs of Ukraine's armed forces." I request a full copy of the document constituting this statment of intent.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Michael Tracey

title: Dispatch Supervisor of NothCom on 12.5.2023 (Palm Beach Gardens Police Department)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

Can you please provide the names and ID numbers for the dispatch supervisor(s) working on 12.5.23 their full name and ID number.

If Jamie smith was working, then please also provide any phone call records she may have made (including recordings) and internal audio or radio recordings/intercommunications between her and the dispatchers.

Also, what if the contact information for the city attorney? Name, phone number and email?

If you could please also CC the police chief, deputy chief and city attorney that would be great.


There should not be any fees associated with this request.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Mason C. Turner
561-320-7690
